OL,7,FReeves stressed the decisions made in
OL,8,Fthe spending review are her decisions
OL,9,Fabout the direction of government,
OL,10,Fconcluding her speech by saying:
OL,11,F"These are my choices, these are
OL,12,FLabour's choices, these are the
OL,13,Fchoices of the British people."
OL,15,FShadow Chancellor Sir Mel Stride said
OL,16,F"the chancellor has completely lost
OL,17,Fcontrol", saying Reeves "will need to
OL,18,Fcome back here in the autumn with yet
OL,19,Fmore taxes, and a cruel summer of
OL,20,Fspeculation awaits."
