OL,7,FPaul Johnson, Director of the
OL,8,FInstitute for Fiscal Studies, said:
OL,9,F"The schools settlement in England is
OL,10,Ftight. Strip out the cost of expanding
OL,11,Ffree schools meals, and you get a real-
OL,12,Fterms freeze in the budget.
OL,14,F"With falling pupil numbers, this
OL,15,Fwould in principle allow a rise in
OL,16,Fspending per pupil. Instead, the
OL,17,Fgovernment may have to freeze spending
OL,18,Fper pupil in order to meet rising
OL,19,Fdemand for special education needs
OL,20,Fprovision."
